olive oil
1 carrot
1 potato
1 tomato
½ Onion
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
1 packet Chargrilled Capsicum Relish
2 packet pork loin steaks
1 sachet Herb & Mushroom Seasoning
1 tsp honey
1 packet Baby Leaves
drizzle white wine vinegar

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut carrot and potato into bite-sized chunks. Cut tomato and onion (see ingredients) into wedges.

• Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, combine, Greek-style yoghurt and chargrilled capsicum relish in a small bowl. Season to taste and set aside.
• In a large bowl, combine pork loin steaks, Tuscan herb seasoning and a drizzle of olive oil.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. When oil is hot, cook pork loin steaks until cooked through, 3-4 minutes each side (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).
• Remove pan from heat, add the honey and gently turn to coat. Transfer to a plate, cover and rest for 5 minutes.

TIP: The spice blend will char slightly in the pan, this adds to the flavour!

• When the veggies are done, remove tray from oven and add baby leaves and a drizzle of white wine vinegar. Season to taste.
• Toss to combine.

• Slice pork.
• Divide roast veggie toss between bowls. Top with tuscan pork.
• Top with chargrilled capsicum yoghurt. Enjoy!